# There's is currently only one value defined for Michelle.  This is missing
# a high-gain mode value for Michelle as it is yet to be determined.
    $_GET_SATURATION_LEVEL_{SATURATION} = 100000;

# Podule
# ======

=head1 NAME

_GET_SATURATION_LEVEL_ -- Finds the Michelle saturation level in ADU the current Frame.

=head1 DESCRIPTION

This primitive obtains the Michelle saturation level in ADU for the current
frame.

The saturation level is returned through an argument.

=head1 ARGUMENTS

=over 4

=item SATURATION = REAL (Returned)

The saturation level obtained.

=back

=head1 NOTES

=over 4

=item *

This primitive is only suitable for Michelle.

=item *

It merely uses an approximnate constant.  At present the level is
not well determined.

=back

=head1 AUTHORS

MJC: Malcolm J. Currie (JAC)

